## <a id='major-features'></a>New Features in Ops Manager v1.11.0

### <a id='ops-man-api'></a>Ops Manager API

Operators can now use the API to trigger an installation process only for Ops Manager Director, skipping the deployment of all other products that have pending changes in Ops Manager. For more information about using this Ops Manager API feature, see [Applying Changes to Ops Manager Director](../customizing/deploy-ops-man-director.html).

### <a id='logging'></a>Improved Logging for the Ops Manager VM

Ops Manager v1.11.0 logs all activity of commands on the Ops Manager VM using Audit D. 

### <a id='vm-hardening'></a>Ops Manager VM Hardening

The OpsManager VM is now built on the stemcell. For enhanced security to maintain consistency with industry standards, Ops Manager VMs should now pass security scans with the same success rates as other BOSH-deployed VMs.

### <a id='nsx-integration'></a>NSX Integration

Operators can use OpsManager 1.11 to configure their Bosh Director to talk to NSX.
OpsManager has API endpoints to configure NSX security groups and load balancers on vSphere appliances. For more information on this feature go to [Configuring Ops Manager Director for VMware vSphere](../customizing/vsphere-config.html#vcenter-config).

### <a id='azure-managed'></a>Azure Managed Disk
OpsManager now allows operators to deploy using Azure's new fully managed storage service. 
This new service alleviates users from having to manage storage capacity manually and is a huge new feature on the Azure platform
For more information on how to use the managed disk feature, please go to [Configuring Ops Manager Director on Azure](../customizing/azure-om-config.html)


### <a id='errands'></a>BOSH CLI v2 Support

Ops Manager v1.11.0 supports both the BOSH CLI v1 and the BOSH CLI v2. You can use either version of the CLI to manage your deployment. For more information about the BOSH CLI v2, see the [BOSH documentation](https://bosh.io/docs/cli-v2.html).

### <a id='bosh'></a> BOSH Updates

The following list sections updates in the new BOSH version that are not exposed by Ops Manager, but may be helpful for operators and tile developers for improving their workflows. 
####<a id='operator-bosh'></a> Operators
+ OpsManager no longer reserves 2 IPs for every requested Static IP. 
+ Updating default catalog on AWS to include m4, c4, and r4 instances
+ Integration with upcoming bbr binary for backups/restore
	+ Added `bin/bbr/backup` and `bin/bbr/restore` scripts to director and blobstore jobs
 
####<a id='tile-dev-bosh'></a> Tile Developers
 
+ Integration with CredHub for secure configuration management.
	+ OpsManager deploys a CredHub co-located with the Director VM. Tile Authors can define a variables section in their 1.11 tiles and have all new credentials reside in CredHub.
+ Added variables CLI command to list which variables are in use by a deployment.

+ OpsManager supports a new top level key called `variables` in the product template. Tile Authors can use this variables section to move all new credentials into CredHub.
+ OpsManager supports a new triple parens syntax such that Tile Authors can define accessors in their manifest snippets that must be evaluated by Bosh
LDAP URL validator now allows a space separated list of URLs to be entered (https://github.com/pivotal-cf/installation/blob/releases/1.8/web/app/validators/ldap_url_validator.rb)
+ OpsManager supports a double parens accessor: (( .job\_name.any\_instances )) for determining if a job has any instances
+ OpsManager triple parens supports string concatenation such that If a Tile Author Provides the following in the manifest snippet or in the link section: `key: "prefix-((( basic_pwd )))-suffix"` then it should show up in the manifest as `prefix-((basic_pwd))-suffix`
+ OpsManager exposes the property type in the JavaScript migrations properties hash in addition to the properties

### <a id='bosh'></a> All Director logs go to SysLog

The BOSH Director now sends all logs to SysLog, an external storage tool intended to preserve logs in case of catastrophic deployment loss. 

Learn how to set up SysLog in the _Configuring Ops Manager Director_ topic specific to your IaaS. 

